HEADWORD: Brontozoum
<hw>Bron`to*zo"um</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ thunder + <?/ animal.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An
extinct animal of large size, known from its three-toed footprints in
Mesozoic sandstone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The tracks made by these reptiles are found eighteen
inches in length, and were formerly referred to gigantic birds; but the
discovery of large bipedal three-toed dinosaurs has suggested that they
were made by those reptiles.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bronze</ent>⟦br⟧
